com.pb.sawdust.calculator

Class NumericValuesProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.calculator.NumericValuesProvider
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NumericValuesProvider.ByteValuesProvider, NumericValuesProvider.DoubleValuesProvider, NumericValuesProvider.FloatValuesProvider, NumericValuesProvider.IntValuesProvider, NumericValuesProvider.LongValuesProvider, NumericValuesProvider.ShortValuesProvider

    public abstract class NumericValuesProvider
extends java.lang.Object
    The NumericValuesProvider class provides a structure for getting primitive numeric argument values for use in numeric functions. Even if it naturally holds a different primitive, it will make the appropriate casting (with possible loss of precision) to provide the desired value.
